In his remarks at the Black Leadership Summit, President Trump thanked the attendees and expressed his admiration for their talent and patriotism. He highlighted the achievements of his administration, such as the strong economy, low unemployment rates, and criminal justice reform. He also criticized the Democratic Party and accused them of prioritizing illegal immigrants over African American constituents. The President pledged to protect free speech on college campuses and to explore solutions to prevent social media platforms from restricting conservative voices. He also praised the work of Turning Point USA and the accomplishments of individual attendees. The President concluded his speech by urging the audience to continue fighting for their rights and for the future of America.